Wrong Model

nested_wrong <- lmer(price ~ (1|product) + (1|size), data = winter_clothes)
summary(nested_wrong)
## Linear mixed model fit by REML ['lmerMod']
## Formula: price ~ (1 | product) + (1 | size)
##    Data: winter_clothes
## 
## REML criterion at convergence: 387.7
## 
## Scaled residuals: 
##     Min      1Q  Median      3Q     Max 
## -1.1269 -0.9758 -0.1420  0.5551  2.0980 
## 
## Random effects:
##  Groups   Name        Variance Std.Dev.
##  product  (Intercept) 33.135   5.756   
##  size     (Intercept) 66.001   8.124   
##  Residual              5.365   2.316   
## Number of obs: 81, groups:  product, 3; size, 3
## 
## Fixed effects:
##             Estimate Std. Error t value
## (Intercept)   17.361      5.754   3.017
grid.arrange(qqmath(ranef(nested_wrong, condVar=TRUE))$product, qqmath(ranef(nested_wrong, condVar=TRUE))$size, ncol = 2)
